The paper deals with an online algorithmic problem related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization, specifically the maximum matching problem with recourse. The problem involves maintaining a valid matching while edges of the underlying graph are presented one after the other, and the algorithm can decide to include or exclude an edge under the restriction that at most k actions per edge take place. This problem is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), algorithms (cs.AL), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
